# On-Jetson runtime comparison (AGX Orin) — all VSR architectures

All runtimes executed **natively on the Jetson AGX Orin** (JetPack 5.1.2, CUDA 11.4,
TensorRT 8.5.2.2, onnxruntime-gpu 1.17.0). Latency = pure GPU compute, 200 iters,
identical harness. INT8 calibrated on real thermal frames (IInt8EntropyCalibrator2).

| Model | input | PyTorch-Orin | ONNX-CUDA EP | TRT FP16 | TRT INT8 | INT8 fps | PSNR INT8/FP16 | PSNR ONNX/FP16 |
|---|---|--:|--:|--:|--:|--:|--:|--:|

| espcn_3f | 3f 512x640 | 12.56 ms | 189.40 ms | **1.78 ms** | **1.49 ms** | 672 | 39.53 dB | 72.51 dB |
| vsrbasic_3f | 3f 512x640 | n/a | 434.71 ms | **50.10 ms** | **38.28 ms** | 26 | 57.70 dB | 74.66 dB |
| vsrbasic_7f | 7f 512x640 | n/a | 708.88 ms | **103.40 ms** | **78.12 ms** | 13 | 55.93 dB | 74.53 dB |
| vsrplusplus_7f | 7f 512x640 | n/a | 1774.64 ms | **379.35 ms** | **256.05 ms** | 4 | 53.13 dB | 74.22 dB |

## Notes

- **TensorRT (FP16/INT8) runs natively on the Orin** — no PC fallback. TensorRT was pre-installed; only onnxruntime-gpu was added.
- **ONNX-Runtime CUDA EP is unsuitable here**: the 5D temporal-stacked input forces many nodes onto CPU (+memcpy), so it is far slower than TensorRT.
- The PC-exported INT8 QDQ model does not parse on TRT 8.5 (per-channel + quantized bias); INT8 is therefore (re)calibrated on-device, which is the correct workflow since a TRT engine is hardware/TRT-version specific.
- ONNX models re-saved with `ir_version=9` (`reports/onnx/orin_ir9/`) because onnxruntime 1.17 / TRT 8.5 reject the IR-v10 originals.
